    <fig id="fig14">
      <label>Fig. 14</label>
      <caption>
        <p>Cortical thickness estimation for an 87-year old male volunteer with a sub-capital femoral neck fracture. The maps were produced using the &#x2018;new variable&#x2019; method. (a) and (b) show the contralateral and fractured femurs from the back, (c) and (d) from the front. This demonstrates the feasibility of estimating cortical thickness maps in vivo, even for fractured femurs. The fractured and contralateral maps are reassuringly similar.</p>
